    "description": {
      "zh": "weapon_izhmash_ak74m_545x39",
      "en": "The AK-107 is a Russian 5.45x39mm assault rifle developed from the AK-100-series. It features a 'balanced' operating system, similar to that used in the AEK-971. In this case, the designation AK does not indicate Avtomat Kalashnikova but Alexandrov/Kalashnikov. The revised designation indicates the incorporation of a new gas system, designed by Youriy Alexandrov, for Kalashnikov-pattern rifles."
